{"title":"The Elegant Kona Coco is the Ideal Commuter Bike Under $900","link":"https://bikerumor.com/the-elegant-kona-coco-is-the-ideal-commuter-bike-under-900/","date":1699283874000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1280\" height=\"707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-hero.jpeg\" alt=\"Kona Coco hero\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-hero.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-hero-297x164.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-hero-800x442.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-hero-120x66.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-hero-768x424.jpeg 768w\" /></p>\n<p>Did you wake up this morning and think “Man, I wish I had an affordable bike that I could use as a ‘get-a-round’ commuter bike”? Kona Bicycles may’ve heard that thought, as it introduced the Kona Coco, an affordable, European-styled, year-round commuter. Just what you wanted!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-front-side.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"1076\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-front-side.jpeg\" alt=\"Kona Coco front side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-front-side.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-front-side-297x250.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-front-side-800x673.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-front-side-120x101.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-front-side-768x646.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/Kona Bicycles)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Coco is an elegantly designed step-through bicycle that pays homage to the European commuters we are all familiar with. Equipped with full-length fenders (with mudflaps), and internal cable routing providing a clean aesthetic, the Kona Coco inspires you to get started on that commuter dream. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-chain-guard.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-chain-guard.jpeg\" alt=\"Kona Coco chain guard\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-chain-guard.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-chain-guard-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-chain-guard-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-chain-guard-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-chain-guard-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-chain-guard-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Chaingaurd to keep your pants clean and snag-free.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Alivio-rear-derailleur.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Alivio-rear-derailleur.jpeg\" alt=\"Kona Coco Alivio rear derailleur\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Alivio-rear-derailleur.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Alivio-rear-derailleur-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Alivio-rear-derailleur-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Alivio-rear-derailleur-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Alivio-rear-derailleur-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Alivio-rear-derailleur-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Shimano rear derailleur</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Hydro-brakes.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Hydro-brakes.jpeg\" alt=\"Kona Coco Hydro brakes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Hydro-brakes.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Hydro-brakes-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Hydro-brakes-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Hydro-brakes-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Hydro-brakes-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Hydro-brakes-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Tektro hydraulic brakes</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-down-tube-logo.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-down-tube-logo.jpeg\" alt=\"Kona Coco down tube logo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-down-tube-logo.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-down-tube-logo-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-down-tube-logo-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-down-tube-logo-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-down-tube-logo-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-down-tube-logo-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Clean lines and subtle branding</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This handsome step-through comes spec’d with a Shimano 9-speed drivetrain, hydraulic brakes, puncture-resistant tires, and an included kickstand, making it a great choice for a worry-free commute. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-subtle-branding.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-subtle-branding.jpeg\" alt=\"Kona Coco subtle branding\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-subtle-branding.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-subtle-branding-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-subtle-branding-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-subtle-branding-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-subtle-branding-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-subtle-branding-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Rear-kickstand.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Rear-kickstand.jpeg\" alt=\"Kona Coco Rear kickstand\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Rear-kickstand.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Rear-kickstand-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Rear-kickstand-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Rear-kickstand-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Rear-kickstand-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Rear-kickstand-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Slap a basket on the Coco, paired with a <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/review-tunitas-carryall-basket-tote-137-a-grab-and-go-tote/\">nice bag</a>, and you’ve elevated it from a neighborhood bike/commuter to a utilitarian, errand-grabbing, pick-up groceries on-the-way home kind of bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The step-through, European commuter bikes are fantastic, and useful tools to encourage us all to ride more and drive less. And the Kona Coco makes it really easy at this price point to take the “commuter plunge” and give it a try.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Kona Coco Geometry</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Frame-Geo.jpeg\"><img width=\"842\" height=\"458\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Frame-Geo.jpeg\" alt=\"Kona Coco Frame Geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Frame-Geo.jpeg 842w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Frame-Geo-297x162.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Frame-Geo-800x435.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Frame-Geo-120x65.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-Frame-Geo-768x418.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-geo-numbers.jpg\"><img width=\"1146\" height=\"916\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-geo-numbers.jpg\" alt=\"Kona Coco geo numbers\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-geo-numbers.jpg 1146w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-geo-numbers-297x237.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-geo-numbers-800x639.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-geo-numbers-120x96.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kona-Coco-geo-numbers-768x614.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Kona Coco Retail and Specs</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $829</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Frame Material: Kona 6061 Aluminum Butted</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fork: Kona Project Two Aluminum Disc</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cassette: Shimano HG200 11-32t 9spd</li>\n\n\n\n<li>R/D: Shimano Alivio SGS</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shifters: Shimano Acera</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Brake Levers: Clarks M2 Hydraulic </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Handlebar: Kona Handpant </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Stem: Kona Control</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Saddle: Kona Commuter</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Grips: Kona Key Grip</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rims: Double Wall Alloy</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tires: WTB Horizon Comp 650x47c</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Paint Color: Gloss Dusky Purple w/ Charcoal &amp; Nimbus Decals</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sizes: XS, S, M, L, XL</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.konaworld.com/\">KonaWorld.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/the-elegant-kona-coco-is-the-ideal-commuter-bike-under-900/\">The Elegant Kona Coco is the Ideal Commuter Bike Under $900</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"749ce6b465944157a290f713646a731f522e1d569eff56a4c40f75c4e91e129a","category":"Cycling"}